content: Pull Request on FHIR Core - I did a pull request 2 hours ago and it is still pending - says "some checks haven't completed yet". Any idea why it is taking so long? @Mark Iantorno @Josh Mandel https://github.com/HL7/fhir/pull/1075

No obvious cause of this issue; the build doesn't appear to have kicked off in https://dev.azure.com/fhir-build/build.fhir.org/_build so I clicked "redliver" on the github webhook. If you see this behavior you can try the same (or adding a new commit to trigger this). I'm not sure what the issue is; but it's building now.
(Just took a look -- PR checks are now successfully complete.)
